args:
Hey, Elisanne—can you tell me what
a ＂prime minister＂ is? It came up in
that history book you let me borrow.
Is it like a chief?
Of sorts. A prime minister aids a ruler\nin government affairs.
Gotcha... Thanks! And sorry I keep\nhaving to ask you about this stuff.
Not at all; you have already made great\nstrides in your studies, and I am happy\nto be of help.
It's funny; I've never been one for hittin'\nthe books, but I can't get enough of 'em\nnow! Human stuff is just so fascinating.
Like that romance novel you gave me—\nI haven't finished it yet, but I am HOOKED.\nWill they? WON'T THEY?!
Ha ha, yes, that one is a favorite of mine.\nLet's have a long discussion when you\nhave seen their tale through.
Thank you for helping with the groceries,\nLaranoa.
Of course! Thanks for bringin' me along.\nShopping's a big part of human culture,\nafter all.
Oh! What's that shop selling?\nI've never seen anything like it.
It seems a uniquely human tool.\nShall we take a closer look?
O-oh, it's okay, I know you have things\nto do...
My schedule can cope with some slight\ndelays, especially if they are in service\nto your studies.
The food here is UH-MAZING!\nI see why you recommended it.
The grub's tasty all right—but it's the\ngossip that keeps me comin' back.\nMercs love this place.
Word is the empire's planning to put up\na new checkpoint on the southern highway.
I know of at least one noble up north\nwho won't take too kindly to that...\nThings could get dicey.
See what I mean? Keep yer ears\nopen round here, and the good stuff\npractically falls into 'em. Bwa ha ha!
I know a few folks in particular who\nmake it their business to know everyone\nelse's—want me to introduce ya?
Heck yeah! I gotta see what kinda lowlifes\nyou hang out with on your own time.
Hey now, we're just a few pals what\ntrade stories now'n then, yeah?\nNothin' shady about it!
Nya ha ha, whatever you say!
Dang, that was one heckuva combo!
But you can't beat our teamwork\nthat easily—Rolf!
Wha—when'd he get behind me?! Aaah!
Nya ha ha, nice try boys!\nNow let's go again.
AGAIN?! That's ten already!\nIt's time for a break.

I don't have time for breaks! Everyone here
has such unique fighting styles, and I
wanna be able to share them with the
people back home.

Besides, aren't you the one who said
you'd help however you can? So less
bellyaching, and more arrow nocking!
Let's—*RUMBLE GRUMBLE*
...Heh heh. Looks like I'M the one with\nthe bellyache. What do you say we\nbreak for some food?

Ohmigosh, how is everything Cleo makes
so GOOD? This sandwich is like a smile
on bread. Hey, you wanna trade one'a your
egg sandwiches for a veggie one?
Hmph. Luca's the worst, isn't he Rolf?
So how are the rest of your studies going,\nLaranoa? You've definitely taken quickly\nto our combat techniques.

Really really well, actually. Everyone's
been super great about helping me,
and it feels like every day is full of
new discoveries.
So I'm gonna keep learning and learning,\nand when I'm done my village is gonna be\nTOTALLY souped up!
Ha ha, I think we all share Rolf's\nexcitement.
Yeah... It's gonna be pretty great.
Heh. Well, I realized recently what I like\nabout this place so much.
There are all sorts of people here, but they\nall manage to coexist—happily, even.
So, one day, I want my village to have\na castle like this too.
Hold up—you're not gonna go razin' the\nforest, are you?!
Don't be stupid, Luca—how're we\nsupposed to be a forest village with\nno forest?!
No—I wanna build a tree castle!\nI'll build it on the mother tree—the huge\nsucker that towers next to our village.
It'll be a place where anyone and everyone\ncan live and be happy, together.
Wow, that's a jumbo dream! You plannin'\non bein' the princess of that castle, then?
Hmm... Now that you mention it...\nNya ha ha!
Princess Laranoa... Ha ha ha! \nMan, I can't picture that AT ALL.
You still hungry Rolf?\nTake a few bites of Luca.
A castle like that is a wonderful\nidea—but it won't be easy.

Yeah. I'm not sure how everyone back
home would feel about it; most of 'em
have never even met a human, let alone
shared a village with one.
But I still wanna make it happen.\nSo I've got a favor to ask, Luca.

Will you come and work with me? You may
be a goofball, but you really care about the
future of sylvan society. I could really use
your energy, and your heart.
Look, Laranoa... I want to help you.\nReally, I do. But I gotta stick with\n{player_name}.

If you're ever in a pinch, just call me up
and I'll be there in a flash! I may not be
able to commit to helping you full-time,
but I still wanna pitch in where I can.
But I still need SOME talented lackey\nby my side... Oh!
What if I convince {player_name}\ninstead? Does that mean\nyou come included, Luca?
Sorry Laranoa, but I've got my own castle\nto run.
Even if he didn't, the dude's a PRINCE!
Hmmm, I guess it WOULD be kinda\nrude to make a prince a lackey. Unless...\nNya ha ha!
Oh jeez, what sorta scheme are you\nhatchin' now?
I just thought of the perfect solution—\nget {player_name} to marry me!
The prince of the Halidom and the princess\nof the forest—we could make the whole\nWORLD happy!
Do you even know what you're saying?!
Nya ha ha! You two are hilarious!
I'm only joking, ya dopes!\n...For now, anyway. Heh heh!
All right, break time's over.\nBack to the grind, boys!
